valid for integer comparisons. For i1, it's meaningless, but setting false is
safe.\n\nNow, we must also consider that the vector icmp may have been created
with samesign already set because the scalar icmp had it and the flag was
propagated via `propagateIRFlags`. We need to check `propagateIRFlags` to see
if it propagates samesign. If it does, we need to prevent that for i1.\n\nLet's
search for propagateIRFlags.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): We'll modify the
ICmp case in `vectorizeTree` to clear samesign flag when element type is i1.
