(cast<CmpInst>(VL0)->isSamesign() &&\n
cast<VectorType>(V->getType())->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(1))\n
cast<CmpInst>(V)->setSamesign(false);\n```\nBut we must ensure V is an ICmpInst
(it is).\n\nAlternatively, we can modify `propagateIRFlags` to not propagate
samesign for i1, but that's more invasive.\n\nLet's choose the edit point at
line 15485 after `propagateIRFlags`. We'll add the check there.\n\n5.
Conclusion: The fix ensures that when vectorizing icmp with samesign to i1
vector type, the samesign flag is cleared, preventing poison when signs differ.
This should make the transformation correct.",
